1
00:00:42,626 --> 00:00:43,666
[This drama is a work of fiction.]

2
00:00:43,666 --> 00:00:44,711
[Any resemblance to real persons,
places, or events is coincidental.]

3
00:00:44,711 --> 00:00:45,736
[Scenes with child actors and animals
were filmed safely]

4
00:00:45,736 --> 00:00:47,297
[under professional supervision.]

5
00:00:47,297 --> 00:00:50,876
[One year later]

6
00:00:52,215 --> 00:00:55,104
<i>My part in this story is over.</i>

7
00:01:06,250 --> 00:01:08,785
<i>Deep down, I knew all along.</i>

8
00:01:13,918 --> 00:01:18,586
<i>From the start, I was just a side character,
following someone else's script,</i>

9
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:29,222
<i>caught in a web spun by the people on top.</i>

10
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:07,385
<i>Inside that hell,</i>

11
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:13,808
<i>the worthless dream I carried</i>

12
00:02:14,631 --> 00:02:17,645
<i>didn't stand a chance.</i>

13
00:02:19,959 --> 00:02:21,265
Pull yourself together.

14
00:02:21,265 --> 00:02:23,901
<i>Even so, in that hell...</i>

15
00:02:25,918 --> 00:02:26,939
Pull yourself together!

16
00:02:26,939 --> 00:02:30,950
<i>Should my leaving light
even the faintest flame,</i>

17
00:02:31,818 --> 00:02:33,459
<i>out of this miserable destiny...</i>

18
00:02:33,459 --> 00:02:36,277
For God's sake, pull yourself together.

19
00:02:36,277 --> 00:02:39,792
<i>that alone would've made it all worthwhile.</i>

20
00:02:42,209 --> 00:02:44,172
No.

21
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:49,093
No.

22
00:02:53,626 --> 00:02:55,558
Please...

23
00:03:21,334 --> 00:03:22,792
Sang Ah.

24
00:03:22,792 --> 00:03:24,754
Are you okay?

25
00:03:57,346 --> 00:03:58,906
Simply sharing the same stage

26
00:03:58,906 --> 00:04:01,020
[Final Episode]
was exciting and such a privilege.

27
00:04:01,020 --> 00:04:03,326
Performing with her in particular,

28
00:04:03,326 --> 00:04:05,162
I've received so many wonderful sparks
of motivation...

29
00:04:05,162 --> 00:04:08,751
[Avoid mentions of the late Hwang Jeong Won]
My question is for actress Chu Sang Ah.

30
00:04:08,751 --> 00:04:11,083
While shooting, one of the film's clips

31
00:04:11,083 --> 00:04:14,337
got confused for actual leaked material,

32
00:04:14,337 --> 00:04:16,959
and it became a whole thing.

33
00:04:16,959 --> 00:04:20,000
What was going through your mind at the time?

34
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,219
Not easy, honestly.

35
00:04:21,219 --> 00:04:22,522
[Four Seasons]

36
00:04:22,522 --> 00:04:26,892
I comforted myself by thinking it just proved
how convincing my performance was.

37
00:04:26,892 --> 00:04:29,425
On top of that,
it gave the movie free publicity,

38
00:04:29,425 --> 00:04:31,250
so we tried tracking down who was behind it.

39
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:34,900
[Actress Chu Sang Ah]
The studio tried to give that person a bonus,

40
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:39,022
but they must've gotten nervous
because nobody ever owned up.

41
00:04:39,022 --> 00:04:40,922
Appreciate the response.

42
00:04:40,922 --> 00:04:43,992
Would it be okay to squeeze in one more?

43
00:04:43,992 --> 00:04:47,198
Of course, seems like there's more.
Please, go on.

44
00:04:47,198 --> 00:04:50,123
Much appreciated. Just one more thing.

45
00:04:50,123 --> 00:04:54,628
That intimate scene between the two women
was absolutely stunning...

46
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,217
Hell of a job out there.

47
00:04:58,217 --> 00:05:00,163
Loved the movie.

48
00:05:00,163 --> 00:05:03,269
And getting into the festival, that's huge.

49
00:05:04,459 --> 00:05:05,889
Thank you.

50
00:05:05,889 --> 00:05:07,732
Couldn't have done it without you.

51
00:05:09,250 --> 00:05:11,520
By the way,

52
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:13,264
I read you booked your next project.

53
00:05:13,264 --> 00:05:15,156
That's great news.

54
00:05:16,650 --> 00:05:19,118
You seem to be doing well too.

55
00:05:21,209 --> 00:05:24,449
Son Guk Won's campaign brought me on board.

56
00:05:24,449 --> 00:05:28,210
With the presidential race coming up fast,
things are only going to pile up from here.

57
00:05:30,539 --> 00:05:33,591
Nice. I'll be cheering you on.

58
00:05:35,334 --> 00:05:38,471
We should get moving now.

59
00:05:42,417 --> 00:05:44,810
I appreciate you showing up.

60
00:05:45,542 --> 00:05:47,688
Look after yourself.

61
00:05:50,221 --> 00:05:52,151
Sang Ah.

62
00:06:03,083 --> 00:06:05,834
I've got something

63
00:06:05,834 --> 00:06:08,042
to run by you.

64
00:06:18,521 --> 00:06:20,923
<i>Let's get to your Monday morning headlines.</i>

65
00:06:20,923 --> 00:06:24,584
<i>With the heated showdown
between Doyak Party's Son Guk Won</i>

66
00:06:24,584 --> 00:06:26,720
<i>and Changjo Party's Gu Hong Seo still raging,</i>

67
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:28,680
<i>the latest polls</i>

68
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:32,525
<i>put Candidate Son
at the top in approval ratings.</i>

69
00:06:36,271 --> 00:06:37,814
[The assemblyman has confirmed it]

70
00:06:37,814 --> 00:06:38,828
[Campaign Manager Lee Chan Yong]

71
00:06:48,074 --> 00:06:51,001
[22nd Presidential Election Debate]

72
00:07:01,180 --> 00:07:03,180
Reconsider this, sir.

73
00:07:03,180 --> 00:07:06,593
Voters today are levelheaded and sharp.

74
00:07:06,593 --> 00:07:10,120
Some tearjerker bit about a vintage watch
isn't fooling anyone.

75
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:12,641
Changjo doesn't have proof regardless,

76
00:07:12,641 --> 00:07:14,613
so no matter what they hurl at me,

77
00:07:14,613 --> 00:07:17,100
brush it off as groundless smear tactics.

78
00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:19,572
If I may, sir, just a second.

79
00:07:22,609 --> 00:07:24,069
Sure, that buys us time today,

80
00:07:24,069 --> 00:07:26,608
but it won't turn the tide in our direction.

81
00:07:26,608 --> 00:07:27,918
Winning this election

82
00:07:27,918 --> 00:07:30,700
takes a narrative that hits people in the gut.

83
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:32,542
Once we can predict

84
00:07:32,542 --> 00:07:34,412
what Changjo's throwing at us, like today,

85
00:07:34,412 --> 00:07:36,334
dropping our counter
at precisely the right beat

86
00:07:36,334 --> 00:07:38,333
makes your integrity

87
00:07:38,333 --> 00:07:40,843
and patriotism land even harder.

88
00:07:43,468 --> 00:07:45,888
Fair enough.

89
00:07:45,888 --> 00:07:49,094
Nobody knows their playbook better than you,

90
00:07:49,094 --> 00:07:51,479
considering you were one of them.

91
00:07:56,435 --> 00:07:58,360
Sir.

92
00:08:02,125 --> 00:08:04,443
Tonight will be the spark

93
00:08:04,443 --> 00:08:06,702
that sets off our upward trajectory from here.

94
00:08:27,966 --> 00:08:30,375
Your loyalty, I can't count on.

95
00:08:30,375 --> 00:08:32,603
But that mind of yours, I believe in.

96
00:08:34,264 --> 00:08:36,204
I appreciate that.

97
00:08:48,362 --> 00:08:51,622
Leave the timing to me.

98
00:08:56,786 --> 00:08:58,288
[22nd Presidential Election Debate]

99
00:08:58,288 --> 00:09:01,250
Out of every candidate in this race,

100
00:09:01,250 --> 00:09:04,378
not one has less moral credibility
than Candidate Son.

101
00:09:04,378 --> 00:09:06,876
Between the Daeyang Fund slush accounts,

102
00:09:06,876 --> 00:09:11,378
corporate kickbacks, and abuse of power,

103
00:09:11,378 --> 00:09:13,377
that's only what we already know about.

104
00:09:13,377 --> 00:09:16,097
Imagine what else will turn up
once we start digging.

105
00:09:16,097 --> 00:09:18,450
Is this really the person we'd trust

106
00:09:18,450 --> 00:09:20,143
to carry this nation on his shoulders?

107
00:09:20,143 --> 00:09:23,017
Those recordings from the general election

108
00:09:23,017 --> 00:09:25,524
were confirmed as forgeries.
Didn't we already settle that?

109
00:09:25,524 --> 00:09:27,776
What makes you keep pushing falsehoods

110
00:09:27,776 --> 00:09:29,922
with nothing to back them up?

111
00:09:29,922 --> 00:09:32,705
You plan on dodging this
all the way to the finish?

112
00:09:34,408 --> 00:09:35,954
[Transcript of Daeyang Fund]
What we've gathered alone is

113
00:09:35,954 --> 00:09:37,911
more than enough for a warrant.

114
00:09:37,911 --> 00:09:40,079
There isn't a doubt in my mind

115
00:09:40,079 --> 00:09:43,666
that you're lying to our faces.

116
00:09:43,666 --> 00:09:44,751
Should I be mistaken,

117
00:09:44,751 --> 00:09:47,295
I'll resign from this race

118
00:09:47,295 --> 00:09:51,724
and surrender everything I own.

119
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:56,312
So what are you willing to stake?

120
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:12,459
My grandfather carried this watch

121
00:10:12,459 --> 00:10:16,058
through the independence movement in the 1930s.

122
00:10:16,058 --> 00:10:19,585
It's been our family's
most sacred possession ever since.

123
00:10:26,932 --> 00:10:29,470
Can you see the blood on it?

124
00:10:30,359 --> 00:10:32,334
Should I

125
00:10:32,334 --> 00:10:34,527
really be the symbol of corruption,

126
00:10:34,527 --> 00:10:38,209
some fossil dragging Korean politics backwards,

127
00:10:38,209 --> 00:10:41,888
then I'll walk away from this election today.

128
00:10:41,888 --> 00:10:43,792
- Yet.
- Yet

129
00:10:43,792 --> 00:10:46,292
- Every single day, I hold this watch
- every single day,

130
00:10:46,292 --> 00:10:47,988
- and remind myself that
- I hold this watch

131
00:10:47,988 --> 00:10:49,667
- and remind myself that...
- our forebears built this country

132
00:10:49,667 --> 00:10:51,049
through blood and sacrifice.

133
00:10:51,049 --> 00:10:53,167
our forebears built this country
through blood and sacrifice.

134
00:10:53,167 --> 00:10:54,696
Every fiber of my being

135
00:10:54,696 --> 00:10:56,663
- has gone...
- Every fiber of my being

136
00:10:56,663 --> 00:10:58,450
- into serving this nation.
- has gone into serving this nation.

137
00:10:58,450 --> 00:11:00,410
But

138
00:11:00,410 --> 00:11:03,067
if baseless attacks

139
00:11:03,067 --> 00:11:07,299
and character assassination are your game,
be my guest.

140
00:11:08,067 --> 00:11:11,512
Let the citizens of this nation
decide what's real.

141
00:11:15,717 --> 00:11:18,018
In that spirit,

142
00:11:18,751 --> 00:11:20,959
I'm staking this seat,

143
00:11:20,959 --> 00:11:23,626
[22nd Presidential Election Debate]
every last thing I own,

144
00:11:23,626 --> 00:11:25,314
along with...

145
00:11:25,314 --> 00:11:29,486
a century of my family's devotion

146
00:11:29,486 --> 00:11:31,615
to this country.

147
00:11:36,473 --> 00:11:38,125
Well then, Candidate Gu,

148
00:11:38,125 --> 00:11:40,582
prepared to step down?

149
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,495
Wait.

150
00:11:43,495 --> 00:11:44,621
Just a moment.

151
00:11:44,621 --> 00:11:46,956
All nine minutes of Candidate Gu Hong Seo's

152
00:11:46,956 --> 00:11:49,011
initiative segment have been exhausted.

153
00:11:49,011 --> 00:11:50,418
Candidate Son Guk Won,

154
00:11:50,418 --> 00:11:52,803
the floor is yours for your initiative debate.

155
00:11:58,551 --> 00:12:01,083
[TV debate heats up over allegations]
Thank you.

156
00:12:01,083 --> 00:12:03,941
That was incredible, sir.

157
00:12:03,941 --> 00:12:04,949
Congratulations.

158
00:12:04,949 --> 00:12:07,693
Congratulations, sir.

159
00:12:12,065 --> 00:12:15,902
The watch moment peaked at over 40% viewership.

160
00:12:15,902 --> 00:12:19,879
And the whole thing buried
the ethics scandal completely.

161
00:12:19,879 --> 00:12:22,242
I figured it was old-school,

162
00:12:22,242 --> 00:12:25,279
but the classics never fail.

163
00:12:25,279 --> 00:12:28,088
Born strategist, born showman.

164
00:12:49,978 --> 00:12:51,271
Director,

165
00:12:51,271 --> 00:12:55,125
tonight went perfectly.
Why are we having this conversation again?

166
00:12:55,125 --> 00:12:58,334
<i>If I rush the insurance reform play,</i>

167
00:12:58,334 --> 00:13:01,406
I'm just loading the gun for Gu Hong Seo.

168
00:13:01,406 --> 00:13:03,626
And that gossip floating
around the trading floors,

169
00:13:03,626 --> 00:13:05,202
that I'll hand you

170
00:13:05,202 --> 00:13:09,250
WR Life shares once I'm sworn in,

171
00:13:09,250 --> 00:13:11,815
you don't think the Changjo Party planted that?

172
00:13:11,815 --> 00:13:14,718
Look.

173
00:13:19,130 --> 00:13:21,892
Hey, get it together!

174
00:13:28,350 --> 00:13:30,171
Sir.

175
00:13:30,171 --> 00:13:33,187
<i>You seem to have a short memory
about everything I did</i>

176
00:13:33,187 --> 00:13:36,899
to build you up and carry you here.

177
00:13:36,899 --> 00:13:40,792
Where you go from here is still in my hands.

178
00:13:40,792 --> 00:13:43,872
Don't forget that.

179
00:13:44,908 --> 00:13:47,963
One wrong turn from me,

180
00:13:47,963 --> 00:13:51,998
<i>and you're off the edge. It's that simple.</i>

181
00:13:51,998 --> 00:13:55,623
Chairman Kwon could go any day now,

182
00:13:55,623 --> 00:13:57,584
so quit stalling

183
00:13:57,584 --> 00:14:00,799
and get the inheritance law amendment lined up

184
00:14:00,799 --> 00:14:03,886
before you even sit down in that chair.

185
00:14:03,886 --> 00:14:05,686
We clear?

186
00:14:15,672 --> 00:14:18,991
Who does she think she's playing...

187
00:15:07,100 --> 00:15:08,999
Want a drink?

188
00:15:38,563 --> 00:15:40,447
So,

189
00:15:41,292 --> 00:15:43,910
that thing you said you needed to discuss,

190
00:15:43,910 --> 00:15:45,994
what is it?

191
00:15:51,751 --> 00:15:54,127
I'm going to pry Lee Yang Mi

192
00:15:55,542 --> 00:15:58,423
off of Son's back.

193
00:16:04,334 --> 00:16:05,868
Lee Yang Mi's dropped the mask,

194
00:16:05,868 --> 00:16:09,229
and the cracks between them
are already showing.

195
00:16:09,229 --> 00:16:11,180
Son already knows that even if he wins,

196
00:16:11,180 --> 00:16:15,842
he's just going to be Lee Yang Mi's puppet,

197
00:16:15,842 --> 00:16:18,469
so I'll work on him

198
00:16:18,469 --> 00:16:22,593
and build a financial cushion
to replace Lee Yang Mi's bankroll

199
00:16:22,593 --> 00:16:24,992
when the moment's right.

200
00:16:26,459 --> 00:16:30,562
You're deep inside both Son's
and Lee Yang Mi's circles right now.

201
00:16:31,416 --> 00:16:34,909
You're willing to risk all that? To do what?

202
00:16:34,909 --> 00:16:38,620
If I don't move now,
she's going to eat me alive all over again.

203
00:16:38,620 --> 00:16:40,918
I can't let her ruin

204
00:16:40,918 --> 00:16:43,343
what I've spent my whole life chasing.

205
00:16:44,375 --> 00:16:46,373
And you

206
00:16:46,373 --> 00:16:49,391
can't keep getting stepped on either.

207
00:16:56,375 --> 00:16:58,567
And I...

208
00:17:01,083 --> 00:17:03,697
I want you back too.

209
00:17:13,490 --> 00:17:15,138
After all of it,

210
00:17:15,138 --> 00:17:18,587
I thought I'd lost you for good.

211
00:17:20,833 --> 00:17:22,708
But that year without you,

212
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:26,417
I realized just how much of you was in me.

213
00:17:26,417 --> 00:17:29,132
Getting hit, falling down,

214
00:17:29,132 --> 00:17:32,309
but knowing you were somewhere out there,
looking the same direction...

215
00:17:33,097 --> 00:17:35,937
that's what kept me standing.

216
00:17:45,158 --> 00:17:47,032
Yeah...

217
00:17:48,250 --> 00:17:51,161
I guess we really were alike.

218
00:17:54,907 --> 00:17:58,627
Sleeping alone, waking up alone in this house,

219
00:17:59,955 --> 00:18:02,464
I had the exact same thought.

220
00:18:04,834 --> 00:18:07,852
I was looking too.

221
00:18:07,852 --> 00:18:10,472
A way to destroy Lee Yang Mi.

222
00:18:17,781 --> 00:18:20,690
There's someone I need to see first.

223
00:18:38,367 --> 00:18:40,287
I'm meeting Assemblyman Choi
from the Changjo Party

224
00:18:40,287 --> 00:18:43,088
and giving him something
he can't walk away from.

225
00:18:59,681 --> 00:19:04,686
<i>The Doyak Party's mastermind
never picked up my calls,</i>

226
00:19:04,686 --> 00:19:07,709
<i>and now you come to me. What an honor.</i>

227
00:19:07,709 --> 00:19:09,823
<i>These are original documents</i>

228
00:19:10,500 --> 00:19:13,444
<i>containing part of the testimony</i>

229
00:19:13,444 --> 00:19:16,530
<i>from a key insider in the Daeyang Fund.</i>

230
00:19:16,530 --> 00:19:19,867
<i>Son doesn't even know this exists,</i>

231
00:19:19,867 --> 00:19:22,417
<i>so he can't fight it,</i>

232
00:19:22,417 --> 00:19:26,006
<i>and the impact will be enormous.</i>

233
00:19:26,640 --> 00:19:29,710
<i>If you'd played this
during last year's election,</i>

234
00:19:29,710 --> 00:19:32,596
<i>the whole outcome could've been different.</i>

235
00:19:33,361 --> 00:19:36,867
<i>Why hold it back until now?</i>

236
00:19:36,867 --> 00:19:38,887
<i>Let's just say I was keeping it
for a day like this.</i>

237
00:19:38,887 --> 00:19:40,930
<i>I play the long game too.</i>

238
00:19:40,930 --> 00:19:43,106
<i>That election was never the endgame.</i>

239
00:19:43,106 --> 00:19:45,609
<i>That takes real nerve.</i>

240
00:19:46,792 --> 00:19:50,023
<i>Regardless, the files are password-locked.</i>

241
00:19:50,023 --> 00:19:53,125
<i>Pick the release date with me,</i>

242
00:19:53,125 --> 00:19:55,619
<i>and I'll send over the password.</i>

243
00:20:02,213 --> 00:20:05,212
<i>This is Candidate Gu's handwritten pledge.</i>

244
00:20:08,283 --> 00:20:10,746
[Changjo Party]

245
00:20:10,746 --> 00:20:13,587
[I'll guarantee Bang Tae Seop the No. 3 PR slot]
<i>Proportional seat number three, it's yours.</i>

246
00:20:13,587 --> 00:20:14,924
<i>Under the radar,</i>

247
00:20:14,924 --> 00:20:18,225
<i>but right where the spotlight hits.</i>

248
00:20:22,139 --> 00:20:24,147
<i>Understood.</i>

249
00:20:26,918 --> 00:20:29,069
<i>I'll be waiting for your call.</i>

250
00:20:31,564 --> 00:20:33,375
Once the Changjo Party takes the bait,

251
00:20:33,375 --> 00:20:36,820
they'll set it off right on cue,

252
00:20:36,820 --> 00:20:39,538
and when Son's cornered,

253
00:20:43,952 --> 00:20:48,630
I'll offer to make it go away and cut a deal.

254
00:20:50,159 --> 00:20:51,709
This is a copy of the USB

255
00:20:51,709 --> 00:20:54,052
that Hwang Jeong Won left before she died.

256
00:21:00,608 --> 00:21:02,854
I handed Lee Yang Mi a version

257
00:21:02,854 --> 00:21:05,848
with the dashcam footage wiped,
the part that proves she's the one

258
00:21:05,848 --> 00:21:08,934
behind Park Jae Sang's death.

259
00:21:08,934 --> 00:21:11,645
